-- Russia Has Collected 24.8 Million Tons of Grain From 24% of Area
-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 2012-07-27T17:04:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-27/russia-has-collected-24-8-million-tons-of-grain-from-24-of-area.html
Russia has collected 24.8 million
tons of grain from 24 percent of the total harvesting area, the
 Agriculture Ministry  said in an e-mailed statement.  That compares with 25.3 million tons at the same time last
year, the ministry said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yuliya Fedorinova in Moscow at 
